## Project layout

This project ships with the boilerX baseline:

- Linter + formatter pre-wired
- Pre-commit hook running format + lint on staged files
- Conventional Commits + commitlint
- Tests skeleton (unit / integration / e2e where applicable)
{{#if ciGithubActions}}- GitHub Actions CI: lint → test → build
{{/if}}{{#if dockerEnabled}}- Multi-stage Dockerfile + docker-compose for local dev
{{/if}}- `AGENTS.md` and `.cursor/rules/` so AI agents working in this repo follow your conventions

## Make targets

| Command         | What it does                          |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `make test`     | Run the test suite                    |
| `make lint`     | Run the linter / formatter check      |
| `make run`      | Start the project locally             |
{{#if dockerEnabled}}| `make docker`   | Build the Docker image                |
| `make docker-run` | Run the project under docker-compose |
{{/if}}{{#if evolveEnabled}}| `make evolve`   | Drive `boiler evolve` against this project (uses `{{judgeMetricFile}}`) |
{{/if}}

